Maintainer: Christian Werner <werner.christian@proton.me>
Description: FieldSimR enables simulation of plant breeding field trials at the  plot level. Its 
    core functionality is the generation of spatially correlated plot-level residuals using either 
    bivariate interpolation or a first-order autoregressive process (AR1:AR1). FieldSimR combines 
    the spatial error with a random error at a user-defined ratio. 
    For simulation of plot-level phenotypes, the simulated plot-level error has to be combined 
    with a genotypic value (simulated or data-based). While the simulation of genotypic values is 
    not implemented in the package, FieldSimR provides wrapper functions to facilitate simulation 
    genotypes in a multi-environment field trial setting using the R package 'AlphaSimR'.
